 TIME
 
Date and Time Classes

- Date: Simple class to represent a given time.
	- Do not modify the time inside.
 	- Used for simple time comparisons and string-time conversions
 	
- Calendar: Complex class to be able to manipulate the date and time inside.

Date
- Created as a regular Java object and stores the current time by default.
- Used for
	- Simple string time conversations
	- Comparing dates, times
For all other tasks, Calendar class is used.

 Date date = new Date();
 date.getTime();  // returns the milliseconds from 1.1.1970
 date.before(date2);
 date.compare(date3);
 
